<DetailLayout
  title="Palpitations — Dr Delhasse, Cardiologist"
  description="Heart palpitations: when to see a cardiologist? Discover the causes and management of cardiac rhythm disorders."
  lang="en"
  alternates={{ fr: '/symptomes/palpitations', en: '/en/symptoms/palpitations', de: '/de/symptome/herzrasen' }}
  pageTitleHtml="<span class='text-primary'>Palpitations</span>"
  subtitle="When your heart races"
  heroBg="/images/cardiologie-med-interne.webp"
  heroImage="/images/detail/palpitations.webp"
  heroImageAlt="Palpitations consultation"
  icon="/images/svg/symptomes/Palpitaciones.svg"
  iconAlt="Palpitations"
  breadcrumb={[{label:'Home', href:'/en'}, {label:'Symptoms', href:'/en/symptoms'}, {label:'Palpitations'}]}
  backHref="/en/symptoms"
  backLabel="All symptoms"
  showEmergencyBanner={true}
>
  <p>A heart that beats too hard is not always a sign of emotion. Stress, fatigue, caffeine or alcohol can be the cause. But sometimes a cardiac rhythm disorder or an underlying condition is at play. If these sensations are frequent, bothersome or associated with pain, fainting or breathlessness, a cardiology assessment is essential. Early diagnosis helps identify the source of the problem and establish appropriate management to control heart rhythm and ensure optimal quality of life.</p>

  <p>When in doubt or if symptoms are concerning, it is better not to wait and to consult immediately.</p>
</DetailLayout>
